title: Jackson Pollock Greyed Rainbow Tote
description:
Tote developed from Jackson Pollock’s Greyed Rainbow, 1953, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

The drips, lines, and splatters that made Jackson Pollock's (American, 1912–1956) art so revolutionary are on display on this tote.

  • Dimensions: 15.5 x 12 x 9 in. Strap drop 10 in.
  • Material: Polyester.
  • Interior zippered pocket and snap closure.
